com.github.wuic.nut

Interface Nut

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConvertibleNut
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractConvertibleNut, AbstractNut, ByteArrayNut, CompositeNut, FilePathNut, HttpNut, ImageNut, NotReachableNut, NutWrapper, PipedConvertibleNut, PrefixedNut, TransformedNut, WebappNut

    public interface Nut

    The nut is the fundamental element of WUIC nut. It's represent a nut, generally corresponding to a static (CSS, Javascript, Image). It could be picked thanks to different protocol (FTP, HTTP, cloud, etc).

    The name is the path relative to a location specified by a NutDao which is in charge of nut creations.

    Since:
    0.1.1
    Version:
    1.4
    Author:
    Guillaume DROUET

      • isDynamic

        boolean isDynamic()

        Indicates if this nut has a dynamic content, meaning that it could be changed each time openStream() is invoked. In this case the nut should not be added to any cache and transformation chain should be applied.

        Returns:
        true if content is dynamic, false otherwise
